---
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import yashsharma from "../imgs/yashsharma.png";
// Supports weights 300-700
import "@fontsource-variable/comfortaa";
import "@fontsource-variable/playfair-display";
---

<html lang="en" class="bg-[#EEEEEE] scroll-smooth antialiased">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="y.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>about</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Nav />
    <main class="flex flex-col items-start mx-[35px] mt-[25px] md:mx-[100px] md:mt-[30px]">
      <h class="mb-[15px] text-[16px] md:text-[20px] md:mb-[30px]">
        ABOUT
      </h>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-between space-y-5 xl:flex xl:flex-row xl:items-center xl:w-full xl:justify-between">
        <div class="space-y-2 md:space-y-4 xl:space-y-4 xl:w-[700px]">
          <p class="text-[16px] md:text-[18px]">
            Hello I am Yash Sharma. Welcome to my corner of internet. I am
            currently a sophomore at university studying Mechanical Engineering.
            I have always been interested in Engineering, that's make me pick
            this as a major. I have been tinkering with machines since my
            childhood, there is no count of how many watches, phones, toy cars,
            I have opend till now. The interest in machine probably began when
            my dad bring me a watch and I opened it in a week, he was not happy
            :). We also had a windows xp machine with Pentium Core 2 Duo with
            512MB of RAM, I still have it. I used to spend 3-4hr a day playing
            GTA Vice City and Road Rash. That is where my fascination with
            computers began. I would spend hours just removing and re-placing
            components on the motherboard.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[16px] md:text-[18px]">
            Curiosity has taken me to interesting places in my life and given me
            a lot of opportunities I would not have had otherwise. I believe it
            is an important trait for a person to have. Curiosity guids me to
            amazing opportunities and adventures. In this age of open
            information, there are plenty of guides available on almost any
            subject matter. This makes is simple for someone like me to just
            learn online about topics I am interested in. Whether it's diving
            into physics, programming, robotics and others or trying my hand at
            biology and history, I'm always eager to expand my knowledge. On
            this website, you'll find highlights of my curious journey, from fun
            projects to exciting discoveries. Let's learn together and see where
            curiosity takes us!
          </p>
          <p class="text-[16px] md:text-[18px]">
            Lorem, ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. At, nihil
            nemo consequatur consectetur, ad veritatis laudantium, sapiente
            temporibus nam eum quas? Reiciendis sint dicta ipsum enim nam,
            dolorum pariatur necessitatibus! Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
            consectetur adipisicing elit. Architecto perspiciatis accusamus,
            nisi alias eligendi excepturi expedita suscipit cumque eaque
            praesentium animi corporis totam dignissimos eveniet non, neque
            exercitationem! Nobis officia possimus sunt ullam impedit amet,
            blanditiis quibusdam unde delectus voluptas? Quis laborum velit
            inventore deleniti assumenda, incidunt itaque ducimus, eaque rem,
            delectus repellendus eveniet dolorem excepturi. Suscipit
            consequuntur facilis odio nobis quisquam. Eveniet, quis. Optio qui
            fuga distinctio quo, sint nostrum rerum quae illum saepe quibusdam
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="md:mx-10 md:flex md:justify-center md:bg-[#D9D9D942] md:rounded-[16px] md:shadow-xl">
          <Image
            class="rounded-[8px] drop-shadow-xl"
            src={yashsharma}
            alt="Yash Sharma"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer/>
  </body>
</html>
<style>
  main h {
    color: var(--Light-Mode-LM---Title, #000);
    text-align: center;
    font-family: "Comfortaa Variable", system-ui;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: normal;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
  }
  main p {
    width: auto;
    color: var(--Light-Mode-LM---Para, #585858);
    font-family: "Playfair Display Variable", serif;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 100;
    line-height: 135.292%; /* 33.823px */
  }
</style>
